Transcription.Text: Ladybirds figure in press advertisements, their sale being by the gallon. Advertisements offer eggs of European, Chinese or native forms of mantis. From the day it hatches in the spring until it dies in the late autumn, the praying mantis satisfies its voracity by eating other insects.
